accessibility.info: Accessible seating is available for wheelchairs and companions.  There is a 3 ticket limit for all accessible seating, unless otherwise posted. venues.name: Michigan Theater

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: For information on events at the Michigan Theater call, (734)668-8397
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Michigan Theater Box Office is open one hour prior to show time.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, MasterCard and American Express are accepted forms of payment.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets can be picked up beginning 1 hour prior to event time at the Box Office, bring identification.

venues.parkingDetail: There are numerous parking structures throughout the downtown Ann Arbor area.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: For Accessible Seating please call (734) 668-8397 Ext. 27

generalInfo.childRule: All patrons must have a ticket, although children may be discounted for certain events.

ada.adaPhones: For wheelchair accessible seating, please call 734-668-8397 ext 21 during business hours or leave a message during after hours.
ada.adaCustomCopy:
To better accommodate your needs, Michigan Theater has requested that all accessible seating ticket accommodations be solicited only through their representatives. Please contact a Michigan Theater representative for further help with your ticket purchase.*   Advance ticket purchase may be required. 
 
* Box office information is subject to change.
ada.adaHours: The Michigan Theater Box Office is open one hour prior to show time.
